  "prompt": "What should be my individual subject scores in NEET 2017?",
  "response": "NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) scores can vary based on several factors including the difficulty level of the exam, the performance of other candidates, and the overall scaling process. However, here are some general guidelines for competitive subject scores based on previous years' trends:\n\n1. **Physics:** Aim for a score of 100-150 out of 180.\n2. **Chemistry:** Aim for a score of 120-160 out of 180.\n3. **Biology (Botany + Zoology):** Aim for a combined score of 200-320 out of 360.\n\nIn total, you should target a score in the range of 400-600 out of 720 to be competitive. Higher scores increase the likelihood of securing admission to a good medical college. Remember, this is just a guideline and actual required scores might vary based on quotas, reservation categories, and specific college cut-offs. \n\nTo maximize your chances, it\u2019s best to focus on thorough preparation, understanding concepts deeply, and practicing previous years' question papers and mock tests under timed conditions.",
